{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7a4ca44b-545a-4463-9837-06e5c3614f0e","content":"No files found in the current directory — so here's the general guidance.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` root element pointing to your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <StackLayout Padding=\"20\">\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font Size: {0}'}\" />\n    </StackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThat single `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` attribute is the key change. The compiler now resolves every `{Binding}` inside that scope against `SettingsViewModel` at **build time**.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\n1. **Misspelled or missing properties** (e.g. `{Binding Themee}`) become **compiler errors** — the build fails immediately.\n\n2. **Enable warnings-as-errors** for extra strictness in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <TreatWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatWarningsAsErrors>\n   ```\n\n3. **Scoped `x:DataType`** — if a child element binds to a different type (e.g. inside a `DataTemplate`), set `x:DataType` on that element. Use `x:DataType=\"\"` to opt out and fall back to reflection-based binding where needed.\n\n### Quick checklist\n| Before | After |\n|---|---|\n| No `x:DataType` | `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on root |\n| Errors found at **runtime** (silent failures) | Errors found at **build time** (compiler errors) |\n| Reflection-based (slower) | Compiled (faster) |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d55c7b70-a3bd-4e55-9648-7f37f8102f91","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No files found. The user is asking a general question about converting a MAUI page to use compiled bindings. I'll provide a concise answer explaining how to do it.","outputTokens":581,"requestId":"0434:3D8F5B:BE96BC:D92A48:6A02791E"},"id":"79d4ce46-af6f-46cb-8d55-128e7f0f93a6","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:49:46.247Z","parentId":"47eb7ccf-479c-432e-b5a8-249cb6855163"}
